contentrichtext.text: '''Laguna Verde''' is the Spanish language form of ''green lagoon'' or ''green lake''. There are many places, lakes and lagoons that take this name due to the presence of green colored waters. These include: *[[Laguna Verde, Chile]] *[[Laguna Verde (lake of Chile)]] *[[Laguna Verde (Bolivia)]], salt lake *[[Laguna Verde (Comarapa)]] *[[Laguna Verde, Dominican Republic]] *[[Laguna Verde, Hong Kong]] - a residential complex in [[Kowloon]], Hong Kong *[[Laguna Verde nuclear power plant]], Mexico ==See also== *[[Lago Verde (disambiguation)]] *[[Green Lake (disambiguation)]] {{geodis}}
